#!F-adobe-helvetica-medium-r-normal--18*
#!N 
#!N  #!Rmessage Message #!N #!N Category #!N 
#!N  #!Lcatdbg,dxall754 h Debugging  #!EL  #!N #!N Function #!N #!N Displays a message to 
the user. #!N #!N Syntax #!CForestGreen #!N #!N  #!F-adobe-courier-bold-r-normal--18*   #!N Message( 
 #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   message, type, popup #!EF ) #!EF #!N #!N #!EC #!N 
#!N Inputs #!T,1,91,276,461,646  #!F-adobe-times-medium-r-normal--14*    #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   #!N TAB Name TAB Type TAB 
Default TAB Description #!EF #!N TAB message TAB string TAB none 
TAB message to be displayed #!N TAB type TAB string TAB 
"message" TAB type of information: error, #!N TAB - TAB - 
TAB - TAB warning, or message #!N TAB popup TAB flag 
TAB 0 TAB 0: Do not display message in #!N TAB 
- TAB - TAB - TAB pop-up window #!N TAB - 
TAB - TAB - TAB 1: Display message in pop-up #!N 
TAB - TAB - TAB - TAB window #!N TAB - 
TAB - TAB - TAB #!EF #!N #!N Functional Details #!N 
#!N #!I0 #!N #!N #!I0 #!N  #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*    #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   message #!EF #!EF 
#!I50 #!N specifies the message to be displayed. #!N #!I0 #!N 
 #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*    #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   type #!EF #!EF #!I50 #!N specifies the kind of 
message. Information messages are presented unaccompanied, but error messages are preceded 
by  #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   ERROR #!EF , and warnings by  #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   WARNING #!EF 
. #!N #!I0 #!N  #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*    #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   popup #!EF #!EF #!I50 #!N 
specifies whether the message is to be displayed in a pop-up 
window as well as in the Message Window. In script mode, 
messages are sent to the xterm, regardless of the pop-up setting. 
#!I0 #!N #!N Note: The display of any or all categories 
of message can be prevented by deactivating the appropriate toggle buttons 
in the  #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   Options #!EF pull-down menu of the Message Window. 
